<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Western Areas Dec qtr net profit slips.</title>
<headline>Western Areas Dec qtr net profit slips.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-01-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Quarter to end-December versus preceding quarter</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net profit before capex		  48.97 vs 49.79</p>
<p>    Capital spending			   79.36 vs 70.66</p>
<p>Full name: Western Areas Gold Mining Company Ltd, managed by JCI Ltd.</p>
<p>    Tonnes milled			    737,000 vs 706,000</p>
<p>    Gold output (kg)			   4,832 vs 4,436</p>
<p>    Yield (gram/t)				6.56 vs 6.28</p>
<p>    Cost (rand/kg)			    48,698 vs 47,130</p>
<p>    Revenue (rand/kg)			 56,085 vs 55,186</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said shaft sinking in the South Deep section of the mine has fully recommenced after a succesful recovery from a water inrush.</p>
<p>It said tonnage milled increased by 4.4 pct to 737,000 tonnes as per the planned increase in production buildup. Operations in the areas affected by a fire in the SV2/3 section were returning to normal.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
